        <h2>A New Day Breaks at UCLA</h2>
  <h3>Announcing the UCLA Meyer &amp; Renee Luskin Conference  Center <br>
    Under Construction, To Open August 2016</h3>
<p><strong>Los Angeles, California</strong>, December 8, 2015 â€¦ A new vision of intellectual inquiry,  scholarly collaboration, civic engagement, and breakthrough discovery is taking  shape in the heart of the UCLA campus with the construction of the <a href="http://luskinconferencecenter.ucla.edu/">UCLA Meyer and Renee Luskin  Conference Center</a>.&nbsp; The property, which has a planned opening in  August 2016, will be a state-of-the-art learning environment, welcoming  scholars, innovators, and thought leaders to debate and shape ideas that lead  to world-changing solutions. Interest has been so strong that the UCLA Luskin  Conference Center is already accepting reservations from organizations,  associations and companies across the country engaged in academic,  philanthropic, educational and research activities.&nbsp; The  295,000-square-foot Luskin Conference Center, which has topped out and is on  course for its August opening, will offer 254 guest rooms, 25,000 square feet  of meeting space, a restaurant and lounge, and a superb art collection  including many original works from artists affiliated with or passionate about  UCLA.</p>
<p>Thanks to the generous and visionary gift of Meyer and Renee Luskin, the Luskin  Conference Center will set new standards of excellence and achievement. <strong>The  stated mission of the Luskin Conference Center is:&nbsp; To offer an inspired  learning environment to the University and greater global community in a  thoughtfully-designed space that fosters excellence, engagement, inspiration,  and breakthroughs.</strong></p>
<p>The Luskin Conference Center will  draw the best academic minds, medical innovators, scientific researchers,  political leaders, and social visionaries. More than a gathering place, the  conference center will be an incubator of ideas, bringing great minds together  in the center of the spectacular UCLA campus in a new facility designed to  optimize the best in technology to enable productive, inspiring meetings and  far-reaching results.</p>
<p>With 254 spacious guest rooms featuring  views of the historic campus, 25,000 square feet of meticulously planned and highly  versatile conference space, the Luskin Conference Center is designed to educate  and inspire. Floor-to-ceiling windows in nearly every meeting room will feature  views of the beautiful landscapes and iconic architecture of the UCLA campus.  The Luskin Conference Center is&nbsp;anchored by a large multi-purpose  conference hall with seating for up to 750 attendees and up to 500 guests for  banquet-style events.&nbsp; Function spaces include 29 meeting rooms, including  25 well-sized breakout rooms, a tiered classroom with fixed seating for 80 and  a vast outdoor event terrace&nbsp;with stunning views of the campus and  athletic fields.&nbsp; A fully equipped and staffed Business Center will be  available to guests.&nbsp; </p>
<p>UCLA is renowned for its research and  technology and the Luskin Conference Center will offer the most advanced  connectivity, audiovisual equipment and teleconference services available,  supported by a highly trained technical staff.&nbsp; Accommodations and  amenities will be consistent with most full-service hotels. The center&rsquo;s 254  well-appointed guest rooms offer a choice of king or queen beds adorned with  high quality linens, mattress toppers, and comfortable pillows to ensure an  excellent night&rsquo;s rest. All rooms are equipped with complimentary WiFi, flat  screen 42&rdquo; HDTV, docking station for electronic devices, speaker phone with  voicemail, in-room safe, coffee maker, terry robes and earth-friendly  sustainable toiletries. Express Room Service will offer a quick and convenient  dining option. The flavors of the Mediterranean will inspire the innovative  cuisine at PLATEIA, the Luskin Conference Center&rsquo;s restaurant and lounge.  Cuisine will include an array of fresh, seasonal California-grown ingredients,  lean meat, the freshest seafood and artisan breads, pastas and cheeses, accompanied  by fine wines, including several top California vintages. </p>
<p>The UCLA Meyer and Renee Luskin  Conference Center is designed to serve the needs of individuals and groups  attending campus meetings or events; those doing business with UCLA entities; and  University of California faculty, students, staff and other University  affiliates, in accordance with the University&rsquo;s mission of teaching, research  and service. The Luskin Conference Center may be used for educational, research  and philanthropic purposes, and for interviews and recruiting. Guests and  organizations eligible to use the conference center include alumni, visiting  academics, vendors and consultants, companies engaged in philanthropic or  educational initiatives, parents of students and families in the process of  selecting a college. For-profit organizations may use the property within these  parameters.</p>
<p>The UCLA campus enjoys an  exceptional location in Westwood, one of Los Angeles&rsquo; most attractive and  lively areas, noted for its vintage movie theaters, fine shops and restaurants  and the nearby internationally renowned Getty Center. The Luskin Conference  Center is just 10 miles from Los Angeles International Airport (LAX), and 15  miles from Downtown Los Angeles. Hollywood and the beaches of Santa Monica and  Venice are just eight miles away. </p>
<p><strong>About  the UCLA Meyer &amp; Renee Luskin Conference Center</strong></p>
<p>The <a href="http://luskinconferencecenter.ucla.edu/">UCLA Meyer and Renee Luskin Conference  Center</a>, currently under  construction in the heart of UCLA&rsquo;s vibrant campus, offers an inspirational  learning environment in a thoughtfully designed space that fosters excellence,  engagement, inspiration and breakthroughs. Scheduled to open in August 2016,  the UCLA Luskin Conference Center is set amid iconic and historic campus  buildings and the exhilarating backdrop of daily student life. The Luskin  Conference Center is a place where the best academic minds, medical innovators,  researchers, political leaders, and societal visionaries will meet to exchange  ideas that will help shape the world.</p>
<p>Upon  opening, the UCLA Luskin Conference Center will feature 254  beautifully-appointed guest rooms, many with sweeping views of the stunning  campus architecture and beautifully landscaped grounds. With more than 25,000  square feet of versatile and thoughtfully-planned event space, the Luskin  Conference Center will offer some of the most technologically advanced  facilities available within the United States and globally<strong>.</strong>&nbsp; The  gracious guest experience at the Luskin Conference Center will be further  enhanced by a full-service restaurant and lounge, room service for breakfast,  lunch and dinner, on-site professional catering services, well-equipped fitness  center, concierge service, business center, valet parking and complimentary  Wi-Fi throughout the property.&nbsp; The conference center project is  self-sustaining and does not utilize state funding or revenues from student  tuition.&nbsp; For more information, please visit <a href="http://luskinconferencecenter.ucla.edu/">http://luskinconferencecenter.ucla.edu/</a>. </p>
